This paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category as it deals with the visualization of spectral images. It could also belong to the graphics (cs.GR) sub-category as it involves generating images. Additionally, the use of generative adversarial networks (GANs) suggests that it could belong to the artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. Finally, the mention of "structure-preserved" visualizations suggests that it could also belong to the multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category.
